#inline#mFMb_DS_SetTrigger( expression {; idleMode } )/*	What it does:	It sets the formula that will be evaluated in the optionally specified idle mode		Required parameters:	expression: a correct formula. Mind the quoting.		Optional parameters:	idleMode: "safeIlde", "semiSafeIdle" of "unSafeIdle"		returns:		nothing if the idle Mode parameter is correct			could return myFMbutler error 7 / Evaluation Error 1224		notes:		the formula should be in the form:			if ( <condition> ; myFMb_DoScript(<parameters>) ; False )			or			Case (			<condition> ; myFMb_DoScript(<parameters>) ;			<other condition> ; myFMb_DoScript(<other parameters>) ;			... ;			False			)			Due to the nature of the expression parameter, the DoScipt plug-in will not verify the syntax of the 			formula during the mFMb_SetTrigger(), as verifying the formula also triggers it.			If the syntax of the trigger is wrong, the formula will not return False, and the DoScript plug-in will 			make the wrong conclusion and consider the alarm triggered.*/